# 10. 笑顔のショーを

Tsukasa: I have to say, it was pretty clever of Emu to throw our farewell party at Phoenix Wonderland.
Nene: It is where everything began for us.
Nene: Emu said that she came up with a plan, but I wonder what she's gonna have us do today...
Rui: Ah, apologies for the wait.
Robo-Nene: We have arrived seven minutes early.
Tsukasa: Oh, Rui... And Robo-Nene?!
Nene: You brought Robo-Nene?
Rui: This is the first time all four of us are meeting in quite some time. Robo-Nene seemed to want to see all of you.
Robo-Nene: Yes. It is nice to see you two again.
Nene: That's good to hear... Let's have a good time together today, Robo-Nene.
Tsukasa: That just leaves Emu. Knowing her, I doubt she's going to be late or anything...
Rui: Ah, could she be right on cue...?
Nene: Looks like it. Lemme see...
Nene: “I'm running late because we ran into some trouble”...?
Nene: She's also saying that we can start going around the park since it might take a while to deal with...
Nene: What do you think happened?
Rui: She just sent another message. Apparently, something is happening with the Wonder Stage...
Tsukasa: Trouble with the stage...? I suppose Emu's hands are sort of tied here.
Tsukasa: Still, is everything going to be okay...?
Tsukasa: We don't know what's actually going on, but if a show is in danger of getting canceled...
Nene: Isn't there some way we can help...?
Nene: I know going over might just mean us getting in the way. But...
Rui: I agree. We may not know exactly what's happening, but there's a chance we'll be able to provide her with some assistance.
Rui: So, let's go over to where Emu is.
Tsukasa: Yes, let's go!
Emu: Understood. I'll let the Phoenix Stage staff know what's going on.
Staff Member: I'm so sorry, and thank you very much!
Emu: (Which stages do I still need to contact...?)
Nene: Emu!
Emu: Wh-What are you guys doing here...?!
Tsukasa: You said something about running into trouble here. Can you tell us what's going on...?
Emu: Oh, umm... The thing is, the Wonder Stage cast flew over to do a traveling performance...
Emu: But the flight they were supposed to catch this morning got canceled. That means they won't be back in time for today's show.
Robo-Nene: Certain parts of the country experienced rough weather this morning.
Nene: But what do you plan on doing if you know the cast isn't gonna make it back in time...?
Emu: I've been trying to get a hold of cast members from the other stages to fill in for them, but...
Rui: It sounds like you haven't had much success...
Emu: *Nod* They all have their own shows to perform, and they'd have basically no time to practice or rehearse.
Emu: I thought about canceling the show altogether, but I also don't want to disappoint all the guests looking forward to seeing a show at the Wonder Stage.
Tsukasa: I see...
Tsukasa: Based on the backdrops and such, this show is supposed to take place in a forest, yes...?
Rui: It seems like it. Could you show me what props you have available right now, Emu?
Emu: S-Sure, they're over here...
Nene: And these look like all the costumes.
Rui: Yes, I'm seeing some things from when we were still performing here.
Rui: This is the clown's wand, and here's a cape that could be used for the alchemist... Everything's been treated with such care.
Rui: Yes, I believe we have everything we need in order to put on that show...
Emu: What?
Tsukasa: Oh, what a coincidence! I was just thinking the same thing!
Nene: Me too.
Emu: Wh-What are you guys talking about?
Tsukasa: Emu, let us put on a show!
Tsukasa: As luck would have it, we all have plenty of experience performing on this stage.
Tsukasa: Plus, we can use the props and costumes we have right here to put on that show.
Emu: That show?
Tsukasa: Yes. If it's a show the four of us have done before, then we won't need much time to practice...
Tsukasa: Honestly, could you ask for any better replacements than us?
Emu: B-But I invited you guys to Phoenix Wonderland because I wanted you to all have fun and enjoy yourselves...
Rui: That won't be a problem.
Nene: I agree.
Nene: I mean, there really is nothing more fun than us doing shows together.
Tsukasa: And you have guests waiting to see a show, no...?
Tsukasa: Which means we need to make putting smiles on their faces our priority. That is why we perform on stage!
Nene: Let us help, Emu...
Nene: I really want us to do a show together, since it's been so long.
Robo-Nene: I will also help.
Emu: You guys...
Emu: Okay, thanks...!
Tsukasa: Alright, that settles that! Let's start getting everything ready!
Audience: Is it true that Wonderlands×Showtime is doing a show today...?!
Audience: Yeah! It was apparently organized last-minute, but I'm so excited about seeing them do a show again...!
Nene: The crowd's starting to gather...
Tsukasa: Yes, this is exhilarating.
Tsukasa: I honestly wasn't expecting the four of us to stand on this stage together again...
Rui: Me neither...
Emu: Hehe. I'm so excited...!
Emu: Let's go out there and make them all smile from ear to ear☆
Tsukasa: Okay, it's almost time for us to go on. Take your places, and...
???: Hello, everyone! Tonight we have a special performance guaranteed to put a smile on your face♪
???: Are you ready to put on a good show for the audience?
Nene: Huh? What was that just now...?
Rui: Did you also hear it, Nene? Who said those things just now...?
Emu: I don't know, but I feel really encouraged now for some reason... Like they were cheering us on☆
Tsukasa: Yes, there is no doubt that they were here to give us all a boost of energy!
Tsukasa: Let us take this strange phenomenon, go out there and put on an incredible show!
Tsukasa: Alright, without further ado...
Tsukasa: It's time for Wonderlands×Showtime's performance to start!
Robo-Nene: “Once upon a time, there was an eccentric traveling theatre troupe. The troupe consists of a show-offy troupe leader...”
Robo-Nene: “A clown who won't listen...”
Robo-Nene: “And a songstress who can't sing in public.”
Robo-Nene: “The oddball group staged many shows, but they never managed to attract an audience.”
Robo-Nene: “Then one day, as they were traveling through a forest, they encountered an alchemist who was performing a show all alone.”
Children: Haha. They really are all oddballs!
Children: What do you think is gonna happen...?!
Tsukasa: (This show is where everything began for us.)
Tsukasa: (It let us truly get to know each other, and because of that, we were able to grow and perform on stage together...)
Tsukasa: (Now, we just need to do what we did back then. Act, sing and make everybody smile.)
Tsukasa: (On our beloved Wonder Stage...!)
Troupe Leader: “Why aren't you singing now? You sang beautiful songs in the forest before...”
Songstress: “Th-That's because I knew no one else was around...”
Troupe Leader: “Argh! Enough! I'm just saying that you should try singing right now! The villagers have already told me about how incredible your voice is!”
Songstress: “Uhh... I-I'd probably sound terrible right now. But...”
Songstress: “Do you think I can really change...?”
Nene: (My legs wobbled so much when we did this show for this first time...)
Nene: (But I'm not afraid of standing on stage at all now.)
Nene: (The others helped make that change happen.)
Nene: (Because we put on so many different shows together...!)
Songstress: “——————...♪”
Audience: Wow... Her voice is so pretty...
Rui: (It really is beautiful...)
Rui: (I can tell just how much she's been working on her singing.)
Rui: (And it's not just Nene. Tsukasa's acting skills have also improved quite a bit. They've both grown so much as actors...)
Rui: (Hehe. So...)
Rui: (As the director, I need to respond to my actors in kind!)
Alchemist: “At this rate, nobody is going to hear her singing. For our songstress, I'll put together a useful contraption...”
Alchemist: “And how about you? You said you're the leader of your troupe. That must mean you're good at one or two things, no...?”
Alchemist: “How would you feel about doing a scene that involves battling against this dragon contraption? It should make for an excellent show.”
Clown: “Cool! You could do shows about big adventures and stuff☆”
Troupe Leader: “Easily done! Watch as I elegantly take flight!” *Roar*
Children: Wh-Wh-Whoa! That's amazing...!
Children: He got to the other side so fast! And it only took him a couple of leaps!
Nene: (Wow. He was already pretty acrobatic, but his technique is so polished now...)
Rui: (I know we prepared that springboard for him, but still... Those movements were extraordinary.)
Rui: (Not only did he fly incredibly high, he drew the audience's attention by keeping a tight form and moving dynamically to stick the landing...)
Emu: (Hehe. The Wonder Stage is full of smiles and laughter...!)
Emu: (Nene's singing, Tsukasa's acting and Rui's directing are just like old times.)
Emu: (No, they're better and more exciting than ever...)
Emu: (This is so much fun...!)
Troupe Leader: “Noooooooo!!!”
Children: Oh no...! Did he fall...?
Troupe Leader: “Darn it! How long has this hole been here...?”
Troupe Leader: “However, as the leader of the Pegasus Troupe, I am not about to give up! I just need to use the contraption that alchemist made for me and...! Juuuump!”
Children: Oh, he's back! Wait, he has wings now?!
Rui: (Hehe. Thankfully, there's plenty of space beneath the stage.)
Rui: (Despite this stunt being a last-minute addition, Tsukasa did a nice job of falling in... We couldn't have asked for a better reaction from the audience.)
Troupe Leader: “Please, believe me this time! With our next show, we can spread joy to everyone around us!”
Troupe Leader: “So... Won't you join my troupe again?”
Clown: “Then, let's do a show together!”
Clown: “You can sing for us, Songstress, you can dance for us, Troupe Leader, and you can come up with lots of fun ideas for us as the director, Alchemist.”
Songstress: “Spread joy to everyone around us, huh...? We don't really have a choice at this point, do we?”
Troupe Leader: “No, because that is the sole purpose of the Pegasus Troupe!”
Emu: (Things are always so fun and exciting whenever we do a show together...☆)
Emu: (And everything turns all sparkly.)
Emu: (The smiles on the guests' faces, and the Wonder Stage.)
Emu: (That's probably because...)
Songstress: “Come on, Clown! Let's dance together!”
Emu: Together...
Clown: “Okay...!”
Emu: (I'm here with them.)
Emu: (Because I get to stand on stage with them again.)
Emu: (That's why everyone and everything looks a lot more sparkly today...!)
Robo-Nene: “And so, this show was able to add more laughter to the village, moment by moment.”
Nene: (This is the climax...)
Tsukasa: (We've reached the final act before the show comes to a close...)
Emu: (No, I don't want it to end...)
Emu: (But...!)
Rui: (That also means I need to enjoy every second of this...)
Rui: (And make the entire crowd here smile from ear to ear...!)
Rui: (Oh, that's right. We're...)
Nene: (The four of us are chasing after our dreams together...)
Tsukasa: (Alright, there are far too many questions that require answering here... But for now, we need to focus on finishing this show...!)
Emu: (Let's all have fun until the very end!)
Robo-Nene: “And they made shows together forever after...”
Robo-Nene: “The end.”
Tsukasa: (That's right...)
Tsukasa: (This view is truly...)
Tsukasa: Thank you very much for coming to visit the park today!!
Everyone: Thank you very much!
Shosuke: Honestly, I came running over because I heard they were having trouble...
Shosuke: But they're receiving a massive round of applause.
Keisuke: Yes. I'm glad they were able to see their show through.
Keisuke: ...
Shosuke: Keisuke?
Keisuke: Oh, it's just... I hadn't seen them do a show in so long...
Keisuke: I couldn't help but feel moved by their performance...
Shosuke: Yeah, me too...
